Arcus Zensen Fund Form D
The United Kingdom-based Arcus Zensen Fund submitted form D about $8.20 million offering. The date of first sale was 2008-12-31. The raised $8.20 million. The offering is still open. The total private offering amount amount was $8.20 million. This form was filed on 2015-10-16. Arcus Zensen Fund’s clarification was: The Investment Manager is paid customary management fees and non-affiliated Directors are customary directors’ fees, as provided in the Issuer’s offering documents.. 
 Arcus Zensen Fund is based in United Kingdom. The company’s business is Pooled Investment Fund. The D form was filed by Andrew Pegge Director. The company was incorporated more than five years ago. The filler’s address is: Arcus Investment Limited, 28 King Street, 5Th Floor, London, X0, United Kingdom, Ec2v 8Eh. — — Arcus Investment Limited is the related person in the form and it has address: 28 King Street, 5Th Floor, London, X0, United Kingdom, Ec2v 8Eh. Link to Arcus Zensen Fund Filing: 000091957415007416.
Analysis of Arcus Zensen Fund Offering
On average, companies in the Pooled Investment Fund sector, sell 37.80% investment fund interests. Arcus Zensen Fund sold 100.00% of the offering. The average investment offering size is $24.76 million for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund industry sector. The total amount raised is 66.89% smaller than the average for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund sector. 

